# {{.ProjectName}}

Connect a local tool with one plugin repo, then generate the supported outputs you need.

This starter uses job-first language on purpose:

- primary path: connect a local tool
- technical shape: local MCP over stdio without launcher code
- edit only `plugin/`

## First Run

```bash
plugin-kit-ai inspect . --authoring
plugin-kit-ai generate .
plugin-kit-ai generate --check .
{{- if .PrimaryTarget }}
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform {{.PrimaryTarget}} --strict
{{- else }}
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform claude --strict
{{- end }}
```

Then validate any other supported output you plan to ship.

## Editable Source

- `plugin/plugin.yaml`: shared plugin identity and supported outputs
- `plugin/mcp/servers.yaml`: the local tool command, args, and env wiring

## Generated Root Files

- root `CLAUDE.md`, `AGENTS.md`, and `GENERATED.md`: managed guidance files that keep humans and agents focused on `plugin/`
- root `README.md`: managed root pointer while it keeps the tool-owned sentinel
- generated target outputs such as `.mcp.json`, `gemini-extension.json`, or target package directories: regenerated from `plugin/`

